With over 220 million subscribers enjoying great content in over 190 countries, it is an exciting time to work at Netflix. Our efforts have brought Netflix to virtually all countries around the globe, and we are excited to bring even more of our Originals programming to our viewers everywhere.
We are looking for a Legal Coordinator to support a wide array of responsibilities related to the development, production and exploitation of Netflix's Kids + Family and Adult Animation programming (both Film and Series). This role will be primarily responsible for: (a) drafting a wide variety of standard legal documents, including certificates of engagement/authorship, non-disclosure agreements, independent contractor and consultant agreements, key crew and animation production-related agreements, (b) ensuring information flow with cross-functional partners, including summarizing contract obligations, (c) managing and updating dashboards, team status sheets and document management systems and coordinating the execution, distribution and uploading of signed agreements to internal applications as well as distribution to external parties, (d) maintaining legal workflows across productions, and (e) ad hoc assignments and projects as needed by the Studio+ team. The ideal candidate will have entertainment business and/or legal affairs experience in television and/or film, and be willing to handle projects from beginning to end.
The candidate must have excellent communication and organizational skills and must be comfortable coordinating among internal Netflix teams. The scope of the role will also include collaborating with internal and external business partners, producers, production counsel and production partners.

This is an opportunity to be part of a public company with a great consumer brand and to grow within Netflix to help shape the future of entertainment. The ideal candidate will welcome the opportunity to be part of a fast‐paced, entrepreneurial organization.
REQUIREMENTS
The successful candidate will have the following qualifications:
At least 1-3 years of entertainment-based experience at a production company, studio or law firm, with direct experience facilitating and drafting basic production agreements and managing dashboards and trackers;
Basic understanding of guild and union agreements and other production-related labor issues;
The ability to work proactively, independently and reliably under tight timeframes in a fast-paced environment, with an ability to stay calm under pressure;
A high level of organization, detail orientation and ability to time-manage across multiple deadlines;
Fluency with Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint and the Google Suite; and
Animation experience preferred.
In addition, the candidate will possess the following:
Demonstrates good judgment, strong critical thinking skills and the desire and willingness to take ownership and control of projects;
Curiosity and willingness to tackle matters outside their area of expertise;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills (candor, honesty);
Strong analytical (strategic and creative) capabilities and judgment;
Ability to work proactively, independently and reliably under tight time frames in a fast‐paced environment;
Ability to work effectively and collaboratively cross‐functionally, think pragmatically and be solution‐oriented;
Adaptable negotiation style; and
Passion for animation.
