Our Support Professionals are highly-respected and use their skills to keep the wheels turning. Your mission? To help create that legendary Disney magic for our Guests and customers. You’d be part of a dynamic, fast-paced team that does their part to bring smiles to millions, and would work with some of the most creative, intelligent people in the business. “We make magic.” That’s our motto at Walt Disney Parks and Resorts. And it permeates everything we do. At Disney, you’ll help inspire that magic by enabling our teams to push the limits of entertainment and create the never-before-seen! Join us – apply today!

Responsibilities :

Primarily support four Proprietors (Front Office, Food & Beverage, Merchandise and Housekeeping) and their teams at Disney’s Port Orleans Resort including TEAMS upkeep, maintaining Outlook distribution lists, conference room booking, proactive calendar management, management schedules, arranging Zoom meetings, supply ordering and receipt in SAP, creating VIP Arrival cards, onboarding/offboarding leaders, preparing presentations, printing posters, and assisting hourly cast when needed. Of course there are going to be memos and spreadsheets, but this job is very much about people, about forming relationships with your leaders and partnerships with your co-workers, and about understanding how the Disney enterprise is structured. Every day as a Support Professional is different! On any given day you might:
Make an inventory of office supplies, then devise a more efficient way to keep things in stock;
Review your leader’s schedule so you understand the day’s priorities;
Think ahead about little things that can turn into big problems, like building in time to get to/from meetings on our sprawling campus;
Schedule conference rooms, meetings and video chats;
Be ready to throw the entire schedule out the door when an emergency comes up, then pick it up again when the dust settles;
Draft letters and emails on behalf of your leaders;
Prepare regular reports and summaries—you’ll have tasks that you “own” completely, and others that you assist with;
Use team to do the job better, faster, smarter;
Collaborate on projects by conducting research, writing, fact-checking and proofreading;
Assist with on-boarding new employees –you’ll be the “friendly face” that newbies count on to answer all their questions;
Manage purchase orders, service orders, blanket order set up and vendor contacts/quotes;
Assist with events like service anniversary recognition, Quarterly Awards, International Housekeeping Week and much more!

